    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Terminology used by prehistorians for a class of microlithic blades with one edge blunted by a secondary retouch. It is assumed that this was so that they could be held more easily. Backed blades first appeared in the early Upper Paleolithic.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
